                      <span>1</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-03-02</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Being a white upper class male, but more importantly being white, it was often difficult to get through the beginning of this book. Malcolms potent rage and resent toward the white man is extreme, and he helps the reader understand why. You'll read his honest thoughts and experiences of opression and racism. Being born with a physical disability I have seen my fair share of prejiduce and bias. I gained incredible strength from reading how a man named Deroit Red evolved from being a dope dealing street hustler into Malcolm X. It was especially rewarding to read about his personal transformation, and how his views changed over the coarse of his life. Malcolm changed the world through his refusal to be silent, and helped uplift and inspire millions. An important piece of history that every American should be required to read. The insight and courage you will gain is profound! A+++++++</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Great American biography</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
